Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.05,0:00:03.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As bright as a spark,\Nwith a penetratingly precise wit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.05,0:00:04.75,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Once he gets started, you can't stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.75,0:00:06.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today we solve the mystery of the legend!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.49,0:00:08.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The trick and the evidence\Nare beyond your imagination!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.73,0:00:10.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.45,0:00:12.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.45,0:00:15.04,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:39.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We came to an old temple with a five-story pagoda while on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.28,0:01:47.08,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But development of a tourist attraction has brought trouble with the tour company.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.17,0:01:52.21,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the next morning, the president of the tour company, Hideaki Oda,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.21,0:01:55.18,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}was found hanging from the pagoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.03,0:01:59.44,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Exactly like the legend surrounding the pagoda...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.12,0:02:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.40,0:02:04.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.72,0:02:06.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is the true crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.90,0:02:09.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If my deduction is right,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.97,0:02:13.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}then Oda{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} didn't kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.80,0:02:14.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.33,0:02:20.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the one who did it was him,\Nthe one who said {\i1}that{\i0} back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.01,0:02:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! What are you doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.19,0:02:39.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that tie pin over there Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.62,0:02:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.86,0:02:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}? Is it Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s tie pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, most likely. Tie pins with diamonds aren't very common.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.85,0:03:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kajimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'd like you to look at this too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:04.64,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yosuke Kajimura (43)\NOda Tours Director\NHotel Oda Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.84,0:03:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, there's no mistake.\NThis belongs to the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.63,0:03:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, you see?! And you accused us of being thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.64,0:03:08.61,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tankai (64)\NGenkai Temple Head Priest
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.64,0:03:08.61,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Jukichi Okabe (55)\NTemple Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.86,0:03:12.86,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shunkai (26)\NTankai's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.31,0:03:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His wallet is probably around here somewhere too...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.41,0:03:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about doing a thorough search?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we know Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't robbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.05,0:03:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His tie pin probably fell when he hanged himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.38,0:03:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the pagoda's over 10 meters from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.50,0:03:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's a bit too far to fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.03,0:03:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could've happened like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.71,0:03:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was deciding whether\Nto kill himself here or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he didn't realize it fell off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.51,0:03:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But tie pins don't fall off so easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.20,0:03:56.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a grass stain on Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s elbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:03:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.61,0:04:01.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the tie pin found here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! So the stain's from the grass around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.09,0:04:10.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'm positive Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} struggled with someone here and fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.54,0:04:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And another thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.83,0:04:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they were taking the body down,\Nthe rope was too short,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.42,0:04:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s feet didn't reach the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, men!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.54,0:04:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you were lowering the body,\Ndid his feet reach the railing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.05,0:04:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, sir! It was about 50 centimeters short!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.78,0:04:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he stood on the railing and\Nhis neck didn't reach the rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.00,0:04:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he couldn't have committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.04,0:04:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! How do you explain this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.65,0:04:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it. It doesn't mean a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.12,0:04:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After a lot of deliberation, Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nclimbed the pagoda to kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.48,0:04:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rope may have been 50 centimeters\Nshort, but there was no turning back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.46,0:05:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, he jumped to the rope\Nand put it over his head!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.36,0:05:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there are so many circumstances\Nindicating it was murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.44,0:05:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's just say for the sake of\Nargument that it was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer would have to carry\Nthe hefty, unconscious Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.31,0:05:21.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,up the narrow stairway, only wide enough for one person, and drag the body!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there was no indication of this\Non either the body or the pagoda!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.06,0:05:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how would the killer hang Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwith a rope that was 50 cm too short?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.88,0:05:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.56,0:05:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder theory is starting\Nto sound far-fetched...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.87,0:05:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.01,0:05:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless it was suicide, there's no way\Nhe could've hung from the pagoda!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.31,0:05:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like you're showing\Neveryone how foolish you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.76,0:05:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're nothing but a mere human.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:06:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll never be able to solve\Nthe mysteries of heaven's wrath!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.64,0:06:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give up and leave this place at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.29,0:06:09.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's true, there are many unanswered questions...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.37,0:06:12.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but there's not enough evidence to prove\Nthis was a murder made to look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.25,0:06:16.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But this is definitely murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.13,0:06:21.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The problem is, how did the killer\Nhang him from the roof of the pagoda?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.93,0:06:27.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Unless I can solve this trick,\Nthis case will be classified as a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.34,0:06:33.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This side was tied to the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.70,0:06:37.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why did the killer use an artillery loop?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.56,0:06:41.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.56,0:06:44.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's how he did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.56,0:06:46.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The fog is finally starting to clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.94,0:06:51.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Using this method, it's possible to tie the rope to the railing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid! You're not supposed to touch the things around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.31,0:06:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.63,0:07:03.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If my theory is correct, then that thing should be around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.26,0:07:08.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.98,0:07:19.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}With this method, Oda{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s death\Ncan be made to look like suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.45,0:07:26.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a fresh scratch on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.43,0:07:44.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Curse, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.53,0:07:48.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You thought up one fantastic trick,\Nusing the legend as your guide!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.46,0:07:50.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But now for the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.22,0:07:53.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've got to find proof he's the murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:08:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was a strange suicide, but it's settled now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.89,0:08:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?\NSomething about it still bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you so stubborn?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.71,0:08:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine, go ahead and write on your report, "Death by Curse".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.53,0:08:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You've got to be kidding!\NIf I do that, I'll be mocked to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:23.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would it be all right if I returned to the hotel now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.71,0:08:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the employees are shaken up by this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.76,0:08:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... I suppose it'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to be on the safe side,\Ngive me your contact number.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.81,0:08:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be at the hotel, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.48,0:08:41.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Look at all that money!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.47,0:08:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.56,0:08:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, you can reach me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.76,0:08:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.42,0:08:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kajimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you sure have a lot of money on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.24,0:08:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s, could it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.60,0:09:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not! His wallet is a different color!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.55,0:09:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This money is for the payment I have to\Nmake to one of the hotel's suppliers today!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.24,0:09:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just a joke, a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.03,0:09:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.66,0:09:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Now that Oda's dead, the plans for\Nthat theme park are dead too, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.50,0:09:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah. If construction isn't stopped right\Naway, our company will go bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.30,0:09:29.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the deed to the temple\Nwill be returned to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.03,0:09:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.54,0:09:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The president gave me\Nthe deed to hold on to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's best if I gave it back to you now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.99,0:09:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that wonderful, Tankai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.42,0:09:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kajimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're a very understanding man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.28,0:09:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was wrong about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.58,0:09:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's very flattering...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the deed, I'm sure it was just a\Nmisunderstanding between the two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.07,0:10:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In lieu of Oda's last act of generosity,\NI will recite a prayer for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.48,0:10:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that my mind's at ease, I can go back\Nto the head temple and resume training.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.15,0:10:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I leave now, I'll get there by evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.72,0:10:13.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll start cleaning the pagoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.54,0:10:17.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:21.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The undeniable, solid proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.26,0:10:25.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's the murderer after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.15,0:10:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.91,0:10:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.29,0:10:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is definitely a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.18,0:10:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I see... Since you're so sure about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.63,0:10:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was forced out of bed so early this morning. I'm so tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.56,0:10:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the hotel and getting some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.91,0:10:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? I'm so sleepy all of a sudden...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.45,0:11:08.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now to put this button speaker\Non the old man's forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.99,0:11:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, this is a suicide case!\NWe're going back to the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.27,0:11:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just one moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo, you are absolutely hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.96,0:11:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you talking about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.71,0:11:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were being given so many hints,\Ndidn't you realize that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.88,0:11:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was no suicide, it was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.36,0:11:43.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.21,0:11:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, why didn't you tell us earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.09,0:11:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I wanted you to\Nsolve it and get the credit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.69,0:11:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize that...\NForgive me for being so dense!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.30,0:11:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.80,0:12:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I want you to pay close attention\Nto my mystery-solving show.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Detective Yokomizo,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.51,0:12:07.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would like to conduct an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.81,0:12:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I enlist the aid of your officers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course you may!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.94,0:12:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Men! Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.69,0:12:15.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.15,0:12:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we'll put a bag weighing\Nthe same as Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.43,0:12:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tie a rope around the neck of the bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.79,0:12:27.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,take the rope up to the fifth tier of the pagoda
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.61,0:12:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and drape it over the edge of the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.40,0:12:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you pass it through the railing\Nuntil it reaches the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.21,0:12:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and tie it to the scrap metal\Nleft on the old unused well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.16,0:12:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to make one side of the\Nscrap metal easier to drop,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it is placed atop a steel rod.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.74,0:12:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Detective Yokomizo,\Npull hard on that string!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.97,0:13:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's hanging! Just like Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.46,0:13:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the identity of your so-called curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rope was charred because it rubbed\Nagainst the edge of the roof, causing friction!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the rope was brand-new,\Nit was frayed because of the friction!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.10,0:13:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since we found the tie pin\Nover there in the grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.06,0:13:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I assume that's where it happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did the killer get the\Nrope around Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.61,0:13:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would have put up a fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but examination of the body\Nshowed no such marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:13:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's a very good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.21,0:14:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me explain things in the order they happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.22,0:14:06.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, the killer called Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to meet him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.09,0:14:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when he saw the opportunity,\Nhe put the noose around Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.06,0:14:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and pulled the string at the same time,\Ndropping the scrap metal into the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.15,0:14:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was pulled up,\Nthe rope around his neck would come off,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.99,0:14:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the killer grabbed his legs, causing him to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.68,0:14:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it was dark, even a slim man
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.48,0:14:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,would be able to topple a large man\Nlike Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who's caught off his guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when the grass stain got on his elbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.10,0:14:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also when the tie pin fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.52,0:14:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had no time to undo the rope, and was pulled up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.83,0:14:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm positive Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was tripped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.36,0:15:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, there's no way he'd get dirt on the heels of his shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.71,0:15:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.22,0:15:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying more than one killer was involved?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.06,0:15:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems you've come across that dilemma, Detective Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.75,0:15:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is a heavy 100 kg!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.36,0:15:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer tried to tie the rope\Nto the railing all by himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.58,0:15:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he wouldn't be able to wind the rope\Naround his hand—only squeeze it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.76,0:15:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The moment the rope was cut,\Nit would be pulled out of his hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.52,0:15:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not possible for him to tie the rope to the railing all by himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.65,0:15:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but it is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.65,0:15:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the killer was alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.07,0:15:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.16,0:15:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly how was it done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.81,0:15:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer used an artillery loop on the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.36,0:15:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Artillery loop?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.13,0:16:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It makes a loop with the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.26,0:16:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've given instructions to the officer on the pagoda. Have him start.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.41,0:16:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Cut the rope and tie it to the railing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.79,0:16:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, he needs to pull the artillery loop in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.83,0:16:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, pass a stick into the loop,\Nmaking a stopper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.58,0:16:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then cut the rope on the outside,\Npull the cut end through the loop and tie it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pull the stick and the ruse is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo!\NThe rope is tied to the railing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.85,0:16:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did it all by himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.66,0:16:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that remains is to collect\Nthe rope that has fallen,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.15,0:16:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and throw it into the old well!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.26,0:16:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this ends my explanation of how\Na legend was used to cover up a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.85,0:16:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only mistake the killer made
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.27,0:17:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was the 50 cm difference between\NOda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s feet and the railing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.17,0:17:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because that's what made me\Nsuspect it wasn't suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.26,0:17:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one capable of rigging all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.94,0:17:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is someone who is familiar with the temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.38,0:17:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on there! Are you insinuating\Nthat one of us is the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.22,0:17:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.35,0:17:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who used this trick and killed Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is you, Kajimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.36,0:17:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What are you talking about, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.26,0:17:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know very much about this temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.51,0:17:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are the general manager of the Hotel Oda,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.54,0:17:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you are also an executive of Oda Tours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.60,0:17:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's easy for you to get the blueprint to this\Nplace—just say it's for the construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.07,0:17:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You calculated the height of the pagoda,\Nthe distance to the well and its depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.06,0:18:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wasn't it you who told the construction\Nworkers to put the scrap metal near the well?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.31,0:18:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you could use it in your scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.11,0:18:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, I may have given the orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.41,0:18:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I did, it was due to\Nsome work-related matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.04,0:18:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you too are aware that I was on\Na business trip last night. I wasn't even here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.57,0:18:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how did you know about Shunkai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s argument last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you came here today, you said:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.06,0:18:35.65,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But last night, when you threatened to\Ntake him to court, he seemed very upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.08,0:18:41.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shunkai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came back last\Nnight right after you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.40,0:18:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.88,0:18:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.35,0:18:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.43,0:18:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president called me on my\Nmobile phone at the hotel in Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.39,0:18:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.77,0:18:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard their conversation\Nright here on these grounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.37,0:19:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you called Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to meet\Nyou here so you could kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.37,0:19:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enough of this foolishness!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.81,0:19:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you have are accusations! Show me\Nsome proof that I was here last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.47,0:19:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have the evidence on you!\NIrrefutable evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.58,0:19:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you sure, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.29,0:19:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Look inside his wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.52,0:19:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.21,0:19:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're talking about the\Npresident's fingerprints on the bills,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.18,0:19:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that won't be proof—\Nhe gave me the money himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.67,0:19:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what am I looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.37,0:19:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It should be stuck between the bills...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A receipt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.01,0:19:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A receipt?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.42,0:19:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... It's a receipt from the Hotel Oda...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.19,0:19:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,September 12, 7:40 PM, for cigars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:20:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. We saw Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} get that receipt\Nlast night while we were having dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.68,0:20:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You left after that, and if you\Nhadn't seen him since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.88,0:20:12.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tell us, how did the receipt\NOda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got end up in your wallet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.54,0:20:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure that after you killed Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.07,0:20:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you saw his wallet lying in the grass,\Nso you kept the money as cash earned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.06,0:20:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you didn't notice the receipt\Nstuck between the bills!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.00,0:20:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you check the receipt,\Nyou'll find Oda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.54,0:20:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What have you got to say, Kajimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.41,0:20:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you still going to deny it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.57,0:20:51.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How stupid. What a silly thing to get caught by.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.99,0:20:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was your motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.81,0:20:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tax evasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.46,0:21:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the company began\Nhaving financial difficulties,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he told me to file a fake financial report.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.69,0:21:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, I profited from the scheme too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.19,0:21:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then I realized he was only letting me profit
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.61,0:21:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because he eventually intended to\Nmake me take the fall for everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.35,0:21:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.30,0:21:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.70,0:21:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before he chopped me off like some lizard's tail,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.46,0:21:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after I'd worked myself\Nto the bone for the company...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a bummer. I thought we\Nwere going to enjoy ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.92,0:23:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is it that every time you're with us,\NDad, we get involved in a case?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.54,0:23:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.39,0:23:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, maybe you're cursed?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.61,0:23:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The temple's right here—\Nwhy don't we have you exorcised?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.69,0:23:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's stupid! I'm a private detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.18,0:23:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm supposed to be involved\Nwith cases! That's what feeds us!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.94,0:23:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Trouble is my business!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.94,0:23:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cases are supposed to follow\Na famous detective around!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.37,0:23:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.37,0:23:41.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's right, he's never lacking trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.66,0:23:50.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}W-What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.16,0:23:59.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If the killer came in through the waterway...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.11,0:24:02.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}then the room should be sopping wet!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.35,0:24:09.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see! So that's why that person did that!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.28,0:24:15.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
